TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,7,1);

if ($a ==4){
   $a =3;
   };

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Rationalize the denominator of expression 
\[\frac{1}{\sqrt{$a}}\] 
i.e., write it in the form of
\[\frac{\sqrt{a}}{b}.\] 
$BR
Your answer for \(a\) is : \{ans_rule(5) \}
$BR
Your answer for \(b\) is : \{ans_rule(5) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans1 = $a;
$ans2 = $a;
ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(num_cmp($ans2));

